## textContent & innerText

Every HTML element has a built-in property called `.textContent`.

You can simply overwrite it using the `=` sign to instantly change the words on the screen!

```javascript
// 1. Select the element
let heading = document.querySelector("h1");

// 2. Overwrite its text property!
heading.textContent = "Welcome to my updated site!";
```

*Note: Many developers also use `.innerText`. For all basic purposes, they do the exact same thing.*

slides.codeSnippet:
let scoreTracker = document.querySelector("#score-data");
let newScore = 5000;

// Update the text property instantly!
scoreTracker.textContent = "Current Score: " + newScore;

