## The Style Object

Every HTML element also has a massive **`.style`** object attached to it. 

Inside this object is every single CSS property you can imagine. To change the background color or font size, just overwrite them!

```javascript
let box = document.querySelector(".box");

// Instantly change the CSS!
box.style.backgroundColor = "blue";
box.style.fontSize = "24px";
box.style.display = "none"; // Make it invisible!
```

*Note: In CSS, properties have hyphens (background-color). In JavaScript, they use CamelCase (backgroundColor)!*
